<title>USA: Shift in US savings to equities normal - Greenspan.</title>
<headline>Shift in US savings to equities normal - Greenspan.</headline>
<dateline>WASHINGTON 1997-03-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Federal Reserve Chairman Alan Greenspan on Tuesday gave the thumbs up to the recent shift in some household savings away from bank deposits to equity mutual funds and other investments.</p>
<p>&quot;That's a normal and desirable expansion of the structure of household balance sheets as the standard of living progressively rises,&quot; he said.</p>
<p>Greenspan also told the House Budget Committee that the outlook for the federal budget was probably the most important factor in determining long-term interest rates, including mortgage rates.</p>
</text>
